title: Melbourne nurse on the pool dive that left her paralyzed
text: 'I couldn't move my body at all': Nurse, 27, describes horrific moment she was left paralysed after diving into a blow up pool from a table at an Australia Day party Carly Wade, from Melbourne, was involved in a horrific accident on Australia Day The 27-year-old dived into a blow-up pool and was left unable to feel her body She was rushed to the Emergency Department, and has been in hospital since Ms Wade talked about her experience and how difficult it has been Friend has set up a GoFundMe page to help to raise funds for the Wade family Published: 05:56 GMT, 21 February 2017 | Updated: 10:41 GMT, 21 February 2017 333 shares
